<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.62/1258: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The King of Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Vittorio Emanuele</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-30">August 30,
                                1939</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am grateful to you for your interest. I have immediately transmitted
                            your message<note n="80" xml:id="d382fn80">See telegram No. 77, August
                                23, 11 a.m., to the Ambassador in Italy, <ref target="#pg_351">p.
                                    351</ref>.</note> to my Government. As is known to all, there
                            has been done and there is being done by us whatever is possible to
                            bring about a peace with justice.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Vittorio Emanuele</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>